      • Device

        public Device(java.lang.String hash,
      Device.Type type,
      DeviceEventListener... listeners)
        Creates a new Device, representing a Device entry from the database.
        Parameters:
        hash - The randomly 8-character hash key of this Device.
        type - The device's type.
        listeners - A variable-length list of event listeners that will watch this device's state.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if hash is null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if hash is not valid.
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if Computer is used as type (not currently supported).

      • getLastUpdate

        public final java.sql.Timestamp getLastUpdate()
        Gets this Device's last update timestamp.
        Returns:
        An sql.Timestamp object representing the date/time the last known update was received. Since Timestamp is a mutable structure, the returned object is a clone, and thus calling any mutators will have no effect on the Device's timestamp data.
